# Aider rules — educari-2027-front

Before any edit, read AGENTS.md at repo root in full. It is the
single source of truth.

The backend repository is at https://github.com/fabiotgk/educari-2027-infra
— its AGENTS.md is the primary reference for conventions.

```bash
aider --read AGENTS.md
```

## Non-negotiables

- Commits in PT-BR with `Co-Authored-By: Ailiv <naoresponda@ailiv.com.br>`
- Multi-tenancy aware: use `useTenant()`; check feature flags
- No hard-coded tenant logic; no `any` in TypeScript
- Server Components by default; `'use client'` only when needed
- Conventional Commits

→ Read AGENTS.md now.
